What is the purpose of adding it to Extensions?  If that is for the client to consume, it would probably be better to return an object graph that includes count information in addition to the results (look at the Relay Connection concept, or make your own return type that has both count and results in it).

It is perfectly valid to have more than one query in a request using aliasing, so you will have problems if it is just thrown into an extension field:
```
{
  firstTen: contacts(limit: 10) {
    name
  }
  firstTwenty: contacts(limit: 20) {
    name
  }
}
```

vs.

```
{
  firstTen: contacts(limit: 10) {
    totalCount
    items { name }
  }
  firstTwenty: contacts(limit: 20) {
    totalCount
    items { name }
  }
}
```

